# Git Workflow Protocol

## Git Protocol
Reference: [docs/git_protocol.md](mdc:docs/git_protocol.md)

## Branch Naming
Pattern: `{agent-name}/work`

Examples:
- localization/work
- engineer/work
- deployment/work
- compliance/work

## Commit Message Format
```
{agent-name}: {brief description}

Examples:
- "localization: Add Hot Rod AN Voice & Tone Guide"
- "engineer: Fix ErrorBoundary generic messages"
- "manager: Coordinate agent assignments after reboot"
```

## Never Commit
- Secrets or credentials
- `node_modules/`
- `.env` files
- Build artifacts (except documented evidence)
- Large binary files

## Evidence Commits
When committing evidence/artifacts:
- Use descriptive commit messages
- Reference task/action item IDs if applicable
- Include timestamp in filename
- Document in feedback file

## Before Pushing
1. Review `git status`
2. Check no secrets exposed
3. Verify evidence is documented
4. Ensure commit message follows format
5. Push to origin: `git push origin {branch-name}`

## Branch Cleanup
Reference Git Cleanup agent for repository maintenance.
